{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Have a set maximum amount for child maintenance per child.",
        "additional_details": "I don\u2019t get why just because the paying parents wage increases them the child maintenance increases. A child\u2019s needs do not change regardless of a parents income. Some children do not receive any maintenance whilst others receive more then some adults monthly income. There should be a cap set per child and a set cap for more then one as people are still receiving the same on universal credit which doesn\u2019t get effected regardless of what maintenance another parent gets. It doesn\u2019t seem fair.",
        "background": "Stop increasing child maintenance due to a paying parent earning more",
